Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tiraspol BASAPRESS, 7/2/1994 -- From our special 
correspondent: A group of over 40 former officers of the Russian 
Ministry of Security who had been fired due to the ministry's 
reorganization came today in Tiraspol. They were engaged by the 
Dniester ministries of interior and security. Well-informed 
sources in Tiraspol told BASA that the transfer of former 
Russian KGB officers to Tiraspol was organized with the help of 
the Russian Democratic Liberal Party led by Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy. 

